questions = [
    ("Tell me about yourself.", "Easy", "Education, skills, projects, communication, and career goal.", "I am a B.Tech student interested in technology, problem solving, and continuous learning. I have worked on academic projects where I used my skills to solve practical problems. I am looking for an opportunity where I can learn, contribute, and grow professionally.", ["Giving only name and college", "Talking too much personal information", "Not mentioning skills or goals"], ["Can you explain one project from your resume?", "Why are you interested in this role?"]),
    ("What are your strengths?", "Easy", "Self-awareness, confidence, and strengths relevant to the role.", "One of my strengths is quick learning. When I face a new concept or tool, I try to understand it step by step and practice it through small tasks or projects. This helps me improve continuously.", ["Listing too many strengths", "No real example", "Overconfidence"], ["Can you give an example of this strength?", "How will this strength help in this job?"]),
    ("What is your biggest weakness?", "Easy", "Honesty, improvement mindset, and self-awareness.", "One weakness I am improving is public speaking. Earlier I felt nervous while speaking in front of others, but I started practicing presentations and participating in discussions to build confidence.", ["Saying I have no weakness", "Mentioning a serious job-related weakness", "Not explaining improvement"], ["What steps are you taking to improve?", "How much progress have you made?"]),
    ("Why should we hire you?", "Medium", "Role fit, confidence, skills, learning attitude, and value to the company.", "You should hire me because I have the required foundational skills, a strong learning mindset, and the ability to work sincerely on assigned tasks. I am ready to learn from seniors and contribute to the team with dedication.", ["Generic answer", "Only saying hardworking", "Comparing negatively with others"], ["What makes you suitable for this role?", "What value can you add to our team?"]),
    ("Where do you see yourself in five years?", "Easy", "Career planning, realistic goals, and growth mindset.", "In five years, I see myself as a skilled professional with strong technical knowledge and good problem-solving ability. I want to take more responsibilities and contribute to impactful projects.", ["Unrealistic goals", "Saying I do not know", "Only focusing on salary"], ["How are you preparing for that goal?", "What skills do you want to improve?"]),
    ("Why do you want this role?", "Easy", "Interest in role, skills alignment, and motivation.", "I want this role because it matches my interests and skills. It gives me a chance to apply what I have learned, work on real-world problems, and grow in a professional environment.", ["No role understanding", "Saying only because I need a job", "Too generic"], ["What do you know about this role?", "Which skill makes you suitable for it?"]),
    ("Why do you want to join our company?", "Medium", "Company research, genuine interest, and alignment.", "I want to join your company because it provides good learning opportunities, works on meaningful projects, and has a professional environment where I can grow while contributing to team goals.", ["No company research", "Mentioning only salary", "Giving same answer for every company"], ["What do you know about our company?", "Which company value do you like?"]),
    ("Describe a challenge you faced and how you handled it.", "Medium", "Problem-solving, responsibility, and learning from difficulty.", "During a project, our team faced a delay because tasks were not clearly divided. I helped organize the work, assigned responsibilities, and followed up regularly. Because of that, we completed the project on time.", ["Blaming others", "No clear action", "No result"], ["What did you learn from that challenge?", "Would you handle it differently now?"]),
    ("Describe a time you worked in a team.", "Easy", "Teamwork, communication, cooperation, and contribution.", "In a college project, I worked with a team where each member handled a specific part. I completed my assigned work, communicated updates, and helped others when needed. This helped us finish the project successfully.", ["Taking all credit", "Not explaining your role", "Saying only we worked together"], ["What was your exact contribution?", "How did you handle team coordination?"]),
    ("How do you handle pressure?", "Medium", "Stress management, prioritization, and calm decision-making.", "I handle pressure by staying calm, listing tasks based on priority, and completing them step by step. I also avoid panic by focusing on solutions instead of problems.", ["Saying I never feel pressure", "No example", "Negative attitude"], ["Can you share an example?", "How do you manage deadlines?"]),
    ("Tell me about a leadership experience.", "Medium", "Initiative, responsibility, decision-making, and people management.", "During a college activity, I coordinated a small team. I divided tasks, communicated clearly, and ensured everyone completed their work. The activity was completed successfully.", ["Only mentioning title", "No action explained", "No result"], ["What leadership style did you follow?", "What challenge did you face as a leader?"]),
    ("How do you handle criticism?", "Medium", "Maturity, openness to feedback, and improvement.", "I take criticism as an opportunity to improve. First, I listen carefully, understand the mistake, and then work on correcting it. Feedback helps me become better.", ["Taking criticism personally", "Ignoring feedback", "Arguing"], ["Can you give an example?", "What feedback helped you improve?"]),
    ("Describe a time you failed.", "Medium", "Honesty, accountability, and learning mindset.", "Once I could not complete a task properly because I underestimated the time required. I learned to plan better, divide work into smaller steps, and start earlier.", ["Blaming others", "Choosing fake failure", "No learning"], ["What did you learn from it?", "How did you avoid repeating it?"]),
    ("What motivates you?", "Easy", "Personal drive, learning attitude, and goal orientation.", "I am motivated by learning new things and improving myself. When I complete a task or solve a problem, it gives me confidence to take up bigger challenges.", ["Only saying money", "Very vague answer", "No connection to career"], ["How do you stay motivated during difficult times?", "What motivates you in work?"]),
    ("Are you willing to relocate?", "Easy", "Flexibility and practical readiness.", "Yes, I am willing to relocate if the opportunity helps me learn, grow, and contribute to the organization. I am open to adapting to a new environment.", ["Saying yes without confidence", "Not being honest", "Unclear answer"], ["Which locations are you comfortable with?", "How will you adjust to a new place?"]),
    ("Are you comfortable working in a team?", "Easy", "Collaboration and communication skills.", "Yes, I am comfortable working in a team. I believe teamwork helps us share ideas, divide responsibilities, and complete tasks more effectively.", ["Only saying yes", "No example", "Ignoring individual responsibility"], ["What role do you usually take in a team?", "How do you manage conflicts?"]),
    ("Are you comfortable working independently?", "Easy", "Ownership, discipline, and self-management.", "Yes, I am comfortable working independently. I can understand the task, plan my work, and complete it responsibly while asking for help when needed.", ["Saying only yes", "No ownership shown", "Not mentioning communication"], ["How do you manage your time alone?", "How do you solve doubts independently?"]),
    ("How do you manage your time?", "Medium", "Planning, prioritization, and discipline.", "I manage time by listing tasks, setting priorities, and completing important work first. I also break large tasks into smaller parts to avoid delay.", ["No planning method", "Saying I multitask always", "No example"], ["Which tool or method do you use?", "How do you handle urgent tasks?"]),
    ("What are your short-term goals?", "Easy", "Clarity, skill development, and job readiness.", "My short-term goal is to improve my technical and communication skills, gain practical experience, and perform well in my first professional role.", ["Unclear goal", "Only salary focus", "No skill plan"], ["How are you working on this goal?", "What skill are you learning now?"]),
    ("What are your long-term goals?", "Easy", "Career vision and commitment to growth.", "My long-term goal is to become a strong professional in my field, take ownership of important projects, and contribute to business growth.", ["Too unrealistic", "No career direction", "No connection to role"], ["What steps will help you reach that goal?", "Which area do you want to specialize in?"]),
    ("How do you handle conflicts in a team?", "Medium", "Communication, patience, and problem-solving.", "I handle conflicts by listening to both sides, understanding the issue, and discussing a practical solution. I focus on the project goal rather than personal differences.", ["Taking sides", "Avoiding conflict completely", "Blaming teammates"], ["Can you give an example?", "What if the conflict continues?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you solved a problem.", "Medium", "Analytical thinking, action, and result.", "In a project, we had incorrect output because of data issues. I checked the input step by step, identified missing values, corrected them, and improved the final result.", ["No clear problem", "No action", "No result"], ["What was your exact approach?", "What did you learn?"]),
    ("What makes you unique?", "Medium", "Self-awareness and personal value.", "My learning attitude and consistency make me unique. Even when I do not know something, I try to learn it through practice and improve step by step.", ["Overconfidence", "Generic answer", "No proof"], ["Can you prove this with an example?", "How does it help in work?"]),
    ("How do you prioritize tasks?", "Medium", "Decision-making, planning, and deadline handling.", "I prioritize tasks based on urgency, importance, and deadlines. I complete high-priority tasks first and then move to less urgent work.", ["Doing easy tasks first always", "No method", "Ignoring deadlines"], ["How do you handle two urgent tasks?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("What do you know about our company?", "Medium", "Research, preparation, and interest.", "I know that your company works in this industry and focuses on delivering value through quality products and services. I am interested in the learning opportunities and professional environment here.", ["No research", "Wrong company details", "Too generic"], ["Why does this company interest you?", "Which product or service do you know?"]),
    ("What are your salary expectations?", "Medium", "Professionalism and practical expectations.", "As a fresher, my priority is learning and gaining experience. I am open to the company standards for this role and confident that the offer will be fair based on my skills.", ["Demanding high salary", "Saying anything is fine weakly", "Not being professional"], ["What is more important than salary for you?", "Are you flexible with the offer?"]),
    ("Do you have any questions for us?", "Easy", "Curiosity, interest, and professionalism.", "Yes, I would like to know more about the training process for freshers and what skills are most important to succeed in this role.", ["Saying no", "Asking only salary", "Asking irrelevant questions"], ["What do you want to learn from this role?", "What are your expectations from the company?"]),
    ("How do you define success?", "Medium", "Values, goals, and growth mindset.", "For me, success means continuous improvement, completing responsibilities with quality, and creating positive value for the team or organization.", ["Only money-based answer", "Too philosophical", "No work connection"], ["How do you measure your progress?", "What is one recent success?"]),
    ("How do you handle deadlines?", "Medium", "Planning, discipline, and delivery focus.", "I handle deadlines by understanding the task clearly, dividing it into smaller parts, and tracking progress daily. If any issue comes, I communicate early.", ["Waiting until last minute", "No communication", "No planning"], ["What if you cannot meet a deadline?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you learned something quickly.", "Medium", "Adaptability and learning ability.", "During a project, I had to learn a new tool quickly. I watched tutorials, practiced with small examples, and applied it to the project successfully.", ["No specific example", "Only saying I am fast learner", "No result"], ["What helped you learn fast?", "How do you learn new tools?"]),
    ("How do you stay organized?", "Easy", "Planning and work discipline.", "I stay organized by maintaining a task list, setting priorities, and keeping my files and notes properly arranged. This helps me complete work without confusion.", ["No system", "Messy explanation", "No example"], ["Which tools do you use?", "How do you track progress?"]),
    ("What is your dream job?", "Easy", "Career interest and role alignment.", "My dream job is one where I can apply my skills, solve meaningful problems, learn continuously, and grow into a responsible professional.", ["Mentioning unrelated role", "Too casual", "Only salary focus"], ["How does this role connect to your dream job?", "What skills are needed for it?"]),
    ("What is your greatest achievement?", "Medium", "Achievement, effort, and impact.", "One of my achievements is completing a project where I learned new concepts and applied them successfully. It improved my confidence and practical understanding.", ["No impact", "Very small example without explanation", "Taking fake credit"], ["Why is it important to you?", "What did you learn from it?"]),
    ("How do you handle repetitive tasks?", "Medium", "Patience, consistency, and quality focus.", "I handle repetitive tasks by staying focused on accuracy and looking for ways to improve efficiency. I understand that even repetitive work is important for quality results.", ["Saying I hate repetitive work", "Careless attitude", "No quality focus"], ["How do you avoid mistakes?", "Can you automate repetitive tasks?"]),
    ("What are your hobbies?", "Easy", "Personality, balance, and communication.", "My hobbies include learning new technologies, watching educational content, and improving my skills. These activities help me stay curious and motivated.", ["Mentioning too many hobbies", "Irrelevant details", "No connection to growth"], ["What did your hobby teach you?", "How do you manage time for hobbies?"]),
    ("How do you accept new responsibilities?", "Medium", "Adaptability, ownership, and learning attitude.", "I accept new responsibilities positively. First, I understand the expectations, plan the work, and learn required skills if needed to complete the task properly.", ["Fearful answer", "Overpromising", "No planning"], ["Can you give an example?", "How do you handle unfamiliar tasks?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you helped someone.", "Easy", "Team spirit, empathy, and supportiveness.", "During a project, one teammate had difficulty understanding a task. I explained the concept and shared useful resources, which helped the team complete work faster.", ["Showing superiority", "No result", "Fake example"], ["Why did you help?", "What was the result?"]),
    ("How do you handle mistakes?", "Medium", "Accountability, learning, and correction.", "When I make a mistake, I accept it, understand the reason, correct it, and make sure I do not repeat it by improving my process.", ["Hiding mistakes", "Blaming others", "No learning"], ["Can you share one mistake?", "How did you correct it?"]),
    ("Why did you choose your field of study?", "Easy", "Interest, career direction, and motivation.", "I chose my field because I am interested in technology and problem solving. It gives me opportunities to learn practical skills and build solutions for real-world problems.", ["No clear reason", "Saying parents forced me only", "No career connection"], ["Which subject do you like most?", "How are you applying your knowledge?"]),
    ("Tell me about your final year or academic project.", "Medium", "Project understanding, contribution, and practical skills.", "In my academic project, I worked on solving a practical problem using technology. My contribution included understanding requirements, implementing key parts, and testing the output.", ["Not knowing project details", "Only saying team project", "No contribution"], ["What was your role?", "What challenges did you face?"]),
    ("How do you improve your communication skills?", "Easy", "Self-improvement and practice habits.", "I improve my communication skills by practicing speaking, participating in discussions, reading, and trying to explain concepts clearly in simple language.", ["Saying communication is not important", "No practice method", "No progress"], ["What is your current challenge in communication?", "How do you practice daily?"]),
    ("What type of work environment do you prefer?", "Easy", "Culture fit and adaptability.", "I prefer a professional and supportive work environment where people communicate clearly, learn from each other, and focus on quality work.", ["Too demanding", "Negative about previous environments", "No flexibility"], ["Can you work in a fast-paced environment?", "How do you adjust to new teams?"]),
    ("How do you deal with a difficult teammate?", "Medium", "Patience, communication, and professionalism.", "I try to understand the reason behind the difficulty, communicate respectfully, and focus on the common goal. If needed, I involve a senior for guidance.", ["Arguing", "Complaining directly", "Avoiding the person completely"], ["Can you share an example?", "What if they do not cooperate?"]),
    ("What would you do if you disagreed with your manager?", "Hard", "Professional communication and respect for hierarchy.", "I would first understand my manager's point of view. If I still have a concern, I would explain my perspective respectfully with facts and accept the final decision professionally.", ["Arguing", "Blindly agreeing always", "Ignoring manager instructions"], ["How do you present your disagreement?", "What if your idea is rejected?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you showed initiative.", "Medium", "Proactiveness and ownership.", "During a project, I noticed that our work needed better organization. I created a simple plan, divided tasks, and helped the team track progress, which improved our output.", ["Waiting for instructions", "No result", "Generic answer"], ["Why did you take initiative?", "What was the impact?"]),
    ("How do you handle change?", "Medium", "Adaptability and positive mindset.", "I handle change by understanding the new requirement, staying flexible, and learning what is needed. I believe change is an opportunity to improve.", ["Resistance to change", "Negative attitude", "No example"], ["Can you share a recent change you handled?", "How do you learn during change?"]),
    ("What is your work style?", "Easy", "Self-awareness and working habits.", "My work style is organized and learning-focused. I prefer understanding the task clearly, planning it properly, and completing it step by step with quality.", ["No clear answer", "Too casual", "No example"], ["How do you work under deadlines?", "Do you prefer team or individual work?"]),
    ("How do you handle multitasking?", "Medium", "Prioritization and focus.", "I handle multitasking by listing all tasks, understanding deadlines, and focusing on one important task at a time while tracking the others.", ["Saying I do everything at once", "No priority", "Careless switching"], ["How do you avoid confusion?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("What is more important: speed or accuracy?", "Medium", "Balanced judgment and quality mindset.", "Both are important, but accuracy is more important when quality matters. I try to work efficiently without compromising correctness.", ["Choosing speed always", "Ignoring deadlines", "No balance"], ["How do you balance both?", "Can you give an example?"]),
    ("What would you do if you received unclear instructions?", "Medium", "Clarification, communication, and responsibility.", "If instructions are unclear, I would ask relevant questions, confirm expectations, and then start the task to avoid mistakes.", ["Guessing blindly", "Doing nothing", "Blaming later"], ["What questions would you ask?", "How do you confirm requirements?"]),
    ("How do you handle boring tasks?", "Easy", "Professional attitude and consistency.", "I handle boring tasks by focusing on their importance and completing them carefully. Every task contributes to the final outcome, so I maintain quality.", ["Saying I avoid them", "No professionalism", "Careless attitude"], ["How do you stay focused?", "How do you ensure quality?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you managed a deadline successfully.", "Medium", "Planning, execution, and result.", "During a project submission, I planned the remaining tasks, divided work among team members, and tracked daily progress. We submitted the project before the deadline.", ["No deadline details", "No personal contribution", "No result"], ["What was your role?", "What did you learn?"]),
    ("What would your friends or classmates say about you?", "Easy", "Personality, teamwork, and self-awareness.", "They would say I am sincere, helpful, and willing to learn. I try to support my teammates and complete my responsibilities on time.", ["Overpraising yourself", "No example", "Too casual"], ["Why would they say that?", "Can you give an example?"]),
    ("How do you build relationships with new people?", "Easy", "Communication and social adaptability.", "I build relationships by communicating respectfully, listening actively, and being helpful. I try to understand people and work cooperatively.", ["Being too informal", "No communication approach", "Negative attitude"], ["How do you adjust to a new team?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("What are your expectations from your first job?", "Easy", "Learning mindset and realistic expectations.", "My main expectation from my first job is to learn industry practices, improve my skills, work on real tasks, and contribute sincerely to the team.", ["Only salary focus", "Unrealistic expectations", "No contribution mindset"], ["What do you want to learn first?", "How will you contribute as a fresher?"]),
    ("How do you respond when your idea is rejected?", "Medium", "Maturity and openness.", "If my idea is rejected, I try to understand the reason and learn from the feedback. I stay professional and continue contributing to the team.", ["Taking it personally", "Arguing", "Stopping contribution"], ["Can you share an example?", "How do you improve your ideas?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you made a decision.", "Medium", "Decision-making and responsibility.", "During a project, we had to choose between two approaches. I compared time, difficulty, and expected output, then suggested the approach that was practical for our deadline.", ["No decision explained", "No reasoning", "No result"], ["What factors did you consider?", "Was your decision successful?"]),
    ("How do you deal with stress during exams or projects?", "Easy", "Stress control and planning.", "I deal with stress by preparing early, making a schedule, and focusing on one topic or task at a time. This helps me stay calm and perform better.", ["Panic-based answer", "No method", "Avoiding responsibility"], ["What do you do when stress increases?", "How do you stay focused?"]),
    ("What is your biggest learning from college life?", "Easy", "Growth, teamwork, and responsibility.", "My biggest learning from college life is that consistency and practice are important. I also learned teamwork, communication, and time management through projects and activities.", ["Only fun-related answer", "No professional learning", "Too vague"], ["How will this help in your job?", "Which experience taught you this?"]),
    ("Describe yourself in three words.", "Easy", "Self-awareness and confidence.", "I would describe myself as sincere, curious, and hardworking because I try to learn continuously, complete my work responsibly, and improve from feedback.", ["Random words without explanation", "Overused words only", "No proof"], ["Why did you choose these words?", "Which word best describes you?"]),
    ("What is your approach to learning a new skill?", "Medium", "Learning process and discipline.", "I start by understanding basics, then practice small examples, refer to useful resources, and finally apply the skill in a mini project or task.", ["Only watching videos", "No practice", "No application"], ["Which new skill did you learn recently?", "How did you practice it?"]),
    ("How do you handle competition?", "Medium", "Positive mindset and self-improvement.", "I handle competition positively. I compare my current performance with my previous performance and use competition as motivation to improve.", ["Jealousy", "Negative comparison", "Fear of competition"], ["How do you stay confident?", "What do you learn from competitors?"]),
    ("What does professionalism mean to you?", "Medium", "Work ethics, responsibility, and behavior.", "Professionalism means being responsible, respectful, punctual, honest, and focused on quality work. It also means communicating clearly and meeting commitments.", ["Only formal dressing", "No work ethics", "Too vague"], ["How do you show professionalism?", "Why is it important?"]),
    ("What are your core values?", "Medium", "Integrity, discipline, and personal principles.", "My core values are honesty, continuous learning, respect, and responsibility. I believe these values help me grow and work well with others.", ["Fake values", "No explanation", "Values not connected to work"], ["Which value is most important to you?", "Can you give an example?"]),
    ("How do you handle feedback from seniors?", "Easy", "Respect, learning, and improvement.", "I listen carefully to feedback from seniors, understand the areas of improvement, and apply their suggestions in my next task.", ["Ignoring feedback", "Defensive attitude", "No improvement"], ["What feedback have you received recently?", "How did you apply it?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you were responsible for something important.", "Medium", "Ownership and reliability.", "During a project, I was responsible for preparing the final report. I collected inputs, organized the content, checked errors, and submitted it on time.", ["No responsibility explained", "No result", "No ownership"], ["How did you ensure quality?", "What pressure did you face?"]),
    ("How do you stay updated with industry trends?", "Easy", "Curiosity and continuous learning.", "I stay updated by following educational videos, blogs, LinkedIn posts, and practicing new tools or concepts related to my field.", ["Not staying updated", "Only social media", "No learning routine"], ["Which trend interests you now?", "How often do you learn?"]),
    ("What is your preferred way of communication?", "Easy", "Clarity and communication style.", "I prefer clear and respectful communication. For important tasks, I like written communication along with discussion so that expectations are properly understood.", ["Too casual", "Ignoring documentation", "No clarity"], ["How do you communicate updates?", "How do you handle misunderstandings?"]),
    ("How would you describe a good team member?", "Easy", "Team values and collaboration.", "A good team member is responsible, supportive, respectful, and communicates clearly. They complete their tasks and help the team achieve common goals.", ["Only technical skills", "No teamwork values", "Too generic"], ["Are you a good team member?", "Which quality do you follow most?"]),
    ("How would you handle a task you do not know how to do?", "Medium", "Problem-solving and learning approach.", "I would first understand the requirement, search for reliable resources, try small steps, and ask seniors for guidance if needed.", ["Giving up", "Guessing without learning", "Not asking for help"], ["Can you share a similar experience?", "When do you ask for help?"]),
    ("Do you prefer smart work or hard work?", "Easy", "Balanced thinking and efficiency.", "I believe both are important. Hard work builds consistency, and smart work helps us use the right method to complete tasks efficiently.", ["Choosing only one blindly", "No explanation", "Cliche answer"], ["Can you give an example?", "How do you apply smart work?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you improved something.", "Medium", "Initiative and continuous improvement.", "In a project, I improved the report format by organizing sections clearly and adding better explanations. This made it easier for others to understand.", ["No measurable improvement", "No personal role", "Very vague"], ["Why did you improve it?", "What was the result?"]),
    ("How do you maintain work-life balance?", "Easy", "Time management and healthy routine.", "I maintain balance by planning my work, completing important tasks on time, and giving some time for rest and learning. This helps me stay productive.", ["Ignoring work responsibility", "No planning", "Too personal"], ["How do you manage busy days?", "Why is balance important?"]),
    ("What would you do if you made an error in an important task?", "Hard", "Accountability and corrective action.", "I would immediately inform the concerned person, correct the error, analyze why it happened, and take steps to prevent it in the future.", ["Hiding the mistake", "Blaming others", "Ignoring impact"], ["How would you prevent repeat mistakes?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("How do you handle negative feedback?", "Medium", "Emotional maturity and improvement.", "I handle negative feedback calmly by listening carefully and understanding the reason behind it. I use it as a chance to improve my performance.", ["Feeling discouraged", "Arguing", "Ignoring it"], ["What negative feedback helped you?", "How did you improve?"]),
    ("What is your biggest fear in starting your career?", "Medium", "Honesty and growth mindset.", "My biggest concern is making mistakes as a beginner, but I understand mistakes are part of learning. I am ready to learn, ask questions, and improve quickly.", ["Too negative", "No solution", "Lack of confidence"], ["How will you overcome it?", "What support do you expect?"]),
    ("Why did you apply for this position?", "Easy", "Role interest and preparation.", "I applied for this position because it matches my skills and career goals. I believe this role will help me gain practical experience and contribute to real projects.", ["Applying randomly", "Only needing job", "No role connection"], ["What attracted you to this role?", "How are you prepared?"]),
    ("What do you do when you are stuck on a task?", "Medium", "Problem-solving and communication.", "When I am stuck, I first try to understand the issue, search for solutions, and test possible approaches. If I still cannot solve it, I ask for guidance with clear details.", ["Waiting without action", "Asking without trying", "Giving up"], ["How long do you try before asking help?", "Can you share an example?"]),
    ("How do you handle success?", "Easy", "Humility and growth mindset.", "I handle success with gratitude and learning. I feel happy about the result, but I also analyze what worked well and how I can improve further.", ["Overconfidence", "Ignoring team contribution", "No learning"], ["What was one success you are proud of?", "How did you celebrate it?"]),
    ("How do you handle failure?", "Medium", "Resilience and learning.", "I handle failure by accepting it, understanding the reason, and improving my approach. I believe failure teaches important lessons for future success.", ["Blaming others", "Giving up", "No learning"], ["What failure taught you the most?", "How did you recover?"]),
    ("What qualities do you expect from a manager?", "Medium", "Professional expectations and team understanding.", "I expect a manager to provide clear guidance, constructive feedback, and support for learning. I also value fair communication and trust.", ["Expecting easy work", "Too demanding", "Negative tone"], ["How do you work with different managers?", "What support helps you perform better?"]),
    ("How do you respond to urgent work?", "Medium", "Priority handling and calmness.", "I respond to urgent work by understanding the requirement quickly, prioritizing it, and focusing fully until it is completed. I also communicate progress clearly.", ["Panic", "Ignoring other tasks", "No communication"], ["How do you manage urgency and accuracy?", "Can you give an example?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you adapted to a new situation.", "Medium", "Flexibility and learning ability.", "When I had to use a new tool for a project, I initially found it difficult. I learned the basics, practiced, and adapted quickly to complete my part.", ["No situation", "No learning", "No result"], ["What made adaptation difficult?", "What helped you adjust?"]),
    ("What are you doing to improve yourself?", "Easy", "Continuous learning and self-development.", "I am improving myself by learning technical skills, practicing communication, working on projects, and taking feedback seriously.", ["No improvement plan", "Only saying I am learning", "No specific skill"], ["Which skill are you improving now?", "How do you track progress?"]),
    ("How do you handle distractions?", "Medium", "Focus and discipline.", "I handle distractions by keeping my workspace organized, setting short work goals, and avoiding unnecessary phone or social media usage during study or work.", ["No control method", "Ignoring distractions", "Too casual"], ["What distracts you most?", "How do you stay focused?"]),
    ("How do you ensure quality in your work?", "Medium", "Accuracy, review, and responsibility.", "I ensure quality by understanding requirements clearly, checking my work before submission, testing outputs, and taking feedback for improvement.", ["Submitting without checking", "No review process", "Only speed focus"], ["How do you check mistakes?", "Can you give an example?"]),
    ("What is your decision-making process?", "Medium", "Logical thinking and responsibility.", "I make decisions by understanding the problem, considering available options, comparing pros and cons, and choosing the most practical solution.", ["Emotional decisions", "No analysis", "Depending fully on others"], ["Can you share a decision you made?", "What if your decision is wrong?"]),
    ("How do you handle a misunderstanding?", "Medium", "Communication and clarity.", "I handle misunderstandings by discussing the issue calmly, asking clarifying questions, and confirming the correct information to avoid further confusion.", ["Ignoring it", "Arguing", "Assuming intentions"], ["Can you share an example?", "How do you prevent misunderstandings?"]),
    ("What is your biggest professional goal?", "Easy", "Career ambition and clarity.", "My biggest professional goal is to become a skilled and reliable professional who can handle important responsibilities and contribute to meaningful projects.", ["No goal", "Only money or title", "Unrealistic answer"], ["How will you achieve it?", "What skills are needed?"]),
    ("How do you handle working with people from different backgrounds?", "Medium", "Respect, adaptability, and inclusiveness.", "I respect different backgrounds and try to understand different perspectives. I believe diverse teams help generate better ideas and solutions.", ["Judgmental answer", "No respect", "No example"], ["Have you worked in a diverse team?", "What did you learn?"]),
    ("How do you take ownership of work?", "Medium", "Responsibility and accountability.", "I take ownership by understanding the task clearly, planning it, completing it on time, and being accountable for the result.", ["Only doing assigned work blindly", "No accountability", "Avoiding responsibility"], ["Can you give an example?", "How do you handle mistakes in owned work?"]),
    ("Tell me about a time you communicated clearly.", "Medium", "Communication skill and clarity.", "During a team project, I explained our task plan clearly to teammates, shared updates, and made sure everyone understood their responsibilities.", ["No communication example", "No result", "Too vague"], ["How did clear communication help?", "How do you confirm understanding?"]),
